"{\"uid\": \"scrippsnews.com-sports-paris-2024-olympics-olympics-triathlon-practice-canceled-due-to-seine-river-water-quality-concerns\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The swimming segment of a triathlon practice at the Paris Olympics was canceled Sunday due to concerns over water quality in the Seine River.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 141, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Swimming in Paris' most famed waterway has been banned for over 100 years due to pollution from factory wastewater, sewage, and rain runoff.\", \"from\": 143, \"to\": 283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 155, \"end\": 160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999978174782824, \"rank\": 2.1825264543411174e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the government has spent nearly $1.5 billion to prepare the Seine for the Olympics by fixing old pipes, limiting the amount of untreated wastewater going into the river, and building a wastewater and rainwater storage basin.\", \"from\": 285, \"to\": 518, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RELATED STORY |Will the Seine River be safe to swim in for the Paris Olympics?\", \"from\": 520, \"to\": 598, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A local governmentbulletin published in Junereported a degradation of water quality and increases in E. coli due to rain discharges upstream, raising concerns that the river would not be ready in time for the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 600, \"to\": 823, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But after tests earlier this month showed that conditions had improved, Paris Mayor Anne Hidalgo and other government officials went for a highly publicized dip in the Seine on July 17 to show that it was safe.\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 1034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 896, \"end\": 907, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 908, \"end\": 920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}, {\"begin\": 992, \"end\": 997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999537836500055, \"rank\": 4.621668003141909e-05, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic organizers assured that despite heavy rains earlier this weekend, they expect water quality in the river will improve over the coming days.\", \"from\": 1036, \"to\": 1183, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's triathlon is currently scheduled to begin Tuesday, with the women slated to compete a day later.\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1290, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Officials said contingency plans are in place if needed.\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1348, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"About Scripps News\", \"from\": 1350, \"to\": 1368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1356, \"end\": 1363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/E._W._Scripps_Company\", \"score\": 0.9563653779395115, \"rank\": 0.03442292171245058, \"text\": \"Scripps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/E._W._Scripps_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/E._W._Scripps_Company\"}]}]}"